High on taste, average on protein, October 30, 2014              Vine Customer Review of Free Product (What's this?)      I have tried many different protein bars over the years, with the Quest bars probably being my favorite. I wasn't expecting much from the ZonePerfect bars, but I will have to say that these bars are probably the best tasting protein bars I have ever had. It really is like a candy bar, in that you get a lot of chocolate and a lot of oats. My problem with it, is that you don't get nearly as much protein as other "protein bars," and the third ingredient on the bar is cane syrup. I don't have a problem with cane syrup, except when a protein bar has so much of it that it has more carbohydrates than protein. I think a protein bar should contain the same or less carbs than protein. Otherwise, why not call it a carbohydrate bar? If you're counting your macros and looking to up your protein, you would do better with something else. Although the amount of cane syrup is probably the reason the bar tastes so good. I do like that it has a limited number of ingredients and they are all ingredients I understand, but I will use these more as a treat than a supplement to increase my daily protein intake.               Comment | Permalink
